# ðŸ“‚ Dataset Information - Smart Crop Recommendation

This dataset is used to build a **Smart Crop Recommendation System** using machine learning.  
It contains environmental, soil, and farming data to predict **Crop_Type** and estimate **Crop_Yield**.

---

## ðŸ”¹ Dataset Source

- **Kaggle Dataset:**  
[Smart Crop Recommendation Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/miadul/smart-crop-recommendation-dataset)  

- **Direct Data File:**  
[Data CSV](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/miadul/smart-crop-recommendation-dataset?select=data)  

> Note: Access to the dataset requires a Kaggle account login.  
> All credits belong to the original Kaggle authors and dataset providers.

---

## ðŸ”¹ Dataset Overview

- **Number of rows (samples):** 10,000  
- **Number of columns (features):** 20  
- **Task Type:** Multi-class classification (Crop_Type) & Regression (Crop_Yield)  

---

## ðŸ”¹ Features Description

| Column                       | Type      | Description |
|-------------------------------|----------|-------------|
| N                             | int64    | Nitrogen content in soil |
| P                             | int64    | Phosphorus content in soil |
| K                             | int64    | Potassium content in soil |
| Soil_pH                       | float64  | pH level of the soil |
| Soil_Moisture                 | float64  | Soil moisture percentage |
| Soil_Type                      | object   | Type of soil (e.g., sandy, loamy) |
| Organic_Carbon                | float64  | Organic carbon content in soil |
| Temperature                   | float64  | Average temperature in Celsius |
| Humidity                      | float64  | Average humidity percentage |
| Rainfall                      | float64  | Rainfall in mm |
| Sunlight_Hours                | float64  | Daily sunlight hours |
| Wind_Speed                     | float64  | Wind speed in km/h |
| Region                        | object   | Geographical region of the farm |
| Altitude                       | int64    | Altitude of farm in meters |
| Season                        | object   | Season when crop is grown |
| Crop_Type                      | object   | Target variable: type of crop to be planted |
| Irrigation_Type                | object   | Type of irrigation used |
| Fertilizer_Used                | float64  | Amount of fertilizer used (kg/hectare) |
| Pesticide_Used                 | float64  | Amount of pesticide used (kg/hectare) |
| Crop_Yield_ton_per_hectare     | float64  | Target variable: crop yield in tons per hectare |

---

## ðŸ”¹ Notes

- No missing values present in the dataset.  
- Features include both **numerical** (int/float) and **categorical** (object) types.  
- Target variables:
  - **Crop_Type:** for classification  
  - **Crop_Yield_ton_per_hectare:** for regression / yield estimation  
- Can be used to build **machine learning models** for crop recommendation and yield prediction.

  - **Crop_Type:** for classification  
  - **Crop_Yield_ton_per_hectare:** for regression / yield estimation  
- Can be used to build **machine learning models** for crop recommendation and yield prediction.

